  "texts": [
    "OpenPose 30 utilizes a convolutional neural network (CNN) to extract features from the image and regress all keypoints.",
    "It then connects these keypoints using graph algorithms and other post-processing operations to estimate the human pose.",
    "However, OpenPose is sensitive to image quality and lighting conditions, and it may be affected by background noise and interference.",
    "To address the challenge of significant pose estimation difficulty caused by scale variations, HigherHRNet 2 employs a high-resolution feature pyramid to learn scale-aware representations.",
    "By incorporating multi-scale feature extraction and multi-level feature fusion, HigherHRNet augments the model's resilience and precision in complex scenes and environments with significant variations."
  ],
